SIMPLE: quartern
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quartern
<hw>Quar"tern</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>quarteroun</ets>, <ets>quartron</ets>, F. <ets>quarteron</ets>, the
fourth part of a pound, or of a hundred; cf. L. <ets>quartarius</ets> a
fourth part, quarter of any measure, quartern, gill. See
<er>Quarter</er>, and cf. <er>Quarteron</er>, <er>Quadroon</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A quarter. Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> The fourth part
of a pint; a gill. <sd>(b)</sd> The fourth part of a peck, or of a stone
(14 ibs.).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A loaf of bread weighing about four pounds; --
called also <altname>quartern loaf</altname>.</def>
<rj><au>Simmonds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quarteron</ent>⟦br⟧
